This paper is about detecting privacy leaks in Android applications using static taint analysis. The primary focus is on security and privacy, which falls under the category of "Computer Science and Game Theory" (cs.CR). However, the paper also discusses the use of inter-component data-flow analysis, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper uses algorithms and data structures to perform the analysis, which falls under the category of "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of context propagation to improve the precision of the analysis, which is related to systems and information science (cs.SI).
